The paper discusses training deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in the computer science sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the exploration of structural degrees of freedom during training, which is a topic in the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the method on image classification tasks, which falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
